I AM indebted to the kindness of the Reverend William Iago, of Bodmin‚ for a copy of a Licence (temp. Edw. III), which shows that Bishop Grandisson had contemplated the Ap- propriation of the Rectory of Bridestowe, as well as the Rectories of Bratton[—Clovelly] and Ilsington, to his College of St. Mary of Ottery.
